fr.reflexe.viewshell.api

Annotation Type SystemService


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface SystemService
    Identifies OSGi service interfaces that are generally implemented by the ViewShell application host and made available at runtime.

    Interfaces marked with this annotation may or may not be available (depending on configuration options) and may be added or removed dynamically (for example, when performing hot upgrades or when specific external dependencies are modified).

    Normally, the @SystemService annotation is only applied to interfaces within fr.reflexe.viewshell.api (and subpackages). It is not intended for direct usage in other packages or in implementing classes.

    Note: This annotation is not used as part of the runtime service lookup behavior in OSGi, it is primarily designed as an aid to help implement new components to use within ViewShell. It may be used to automate the creation of plugins by identifying possible dependencies.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
